<inglise> Commission Directive 98/22/EC of 15 April 1998 laying down the minimum conditions for carrying out plant health checks in the Community, at inspection posts other than those at the place of destination, of plants, plant products or other objects coming from third countries </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI DIREKTIIV 98/22/E&Uuml;, milles s&auml;testatakse miinimumn&otilde;uded kolmandatest riikidest toodavate taimede, taimsete saaduste ja muude toodete f&uuml;tosanitaarkontrolli tegemiseks &uuml;henduses mujal kui sihtkohas asuvates kontrollpunktides 15. aprill 1998 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 77/93/EEC of 21 December 1976 on protective measures against the introduction into the Community of organisms harmful to plants or plant products and against their spread within the Community (1), as last amended by Commission Directive 98/2/EC (2), and in particular the penultimate subparagraph of Article 12(6) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 21. detsembri 1976. aasta direktiivi 77/93/EM&Uuml; taimedele v&otilde;i taimsetele saadustele kahjulike organismide &uuml;hendusse kandumise ja seal levimise vastu v&otilde;etavate kaitsemeetmete kohta, (1) viimati muudetud komisjoni direktiiviga 98/2/E&Uuml;, (2) eriti selle artikli 12 l&otilde;ike 6 eelviimast l&otilde;iku, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, if arrangements for the plant health checks of plants, plant products or other objects listed in part B of Annex V to Directive 77/93/EEC coming from third countries are to be operated efficiently, harmonised minimum conditions should be laid down for carrying out these checks at inspection posts other than those at the place of destination; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: kolmandates riikidest toodavate, direktiivi 77/93/EM&Uuml; V lisa B osas loetletud taimede, taimsete saaduste ja muude toodete f&uuml;tosanitaarkontrolli tegemise korra t&otilde;husaks toimimiseks tuleks k&otilde;nealuste kontrollide tegemiseks mujal kui sihtkohas asuvates kontrollpunktides s&auml;testada &uuml;htlustatud miinimumn&otilde;uded; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the minimum conditions laid down for carrying out such plant health checks must take account of technical requirements applicable to the responsible official bodies as referred to in Article 2(1) (g) of Directive 77/93/EEC in charge of the said inspection posts as well as of provisions applicable to facilities, tools and equipment enabling the said responsible official bodies to carry out the required plant health checks; </inglise>
<eesti> selliste f&uuml;tosanitaarkontrollide tegemiseks s&auml;testatavates miinimumn&otilde;uetes tuleb arvesse v&otilde;tta direktiivi 77/93/EM&Uuml; artikli 2 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis g osutatud k&otilde;nealuste kontrollpunktide eest vastutava ametiasutuse suhtes kohaldatavaid tehnilisi n&otilde;udeid ning s&auml;tteid, mida kohaldatakse nende v&otilde;imaluste, t&ouml;&ouml;riistade ja seadmete suhtes, mis v&otilde;imaldavad nimetatud vastutaval ametiasutusel teha vajalikke f&uuml;tosanitaarkontrolle; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Directive are in accordance with the opinion of the Standing Committee on Plant Health, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las alalise taimetervise komitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that the plant health checks referred to in Article 12(6), fourth subparagraph of Directive 77/93/EEC, of plants, plant products or other objects listed in Annex V, part B of the said Directive and coming from third countries, and carried out at inspection posts other than those at the place of destination, satisfy at least the minimum conditions laid down in the Annex to this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tagavad, et kolmandatest riikidest toodavate, direktiivi 77/93/EM&Uuml; V lisa B osas loetletud taimede, taimsete saaduste ja muude toodete nimetatud direktiivi artikli 12 l&otilde;ike 6 neljandas l&otilde;igus osutatud f&uuml;tosanitaarkontrollid, mis tehakse mujal kui sihtkohas asuvates kontrollpunktides, vastavad v&auml;hemalt k&auml;esoleva direktiivi lisas s&auml;testatud miinimumn&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall bring into force the laws, regulations or administrative provisions necessary to comply with this Directive on 1 October 1998. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid j&otilde;ustavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&auml;rgimiseks vajalikud &otilde;igusaktid enne 1. oktoobrit 1998. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall immediately inform the Commission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid teatavad sellest viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> When Member States adopt these measures, they shall contain a reference to this Directive or shall be accompanied by such a reference at the time of their official publication. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikmesriigid k&otilde;nealused meetmed vastu v&otilde;tavad, lisavad nad nendesse meetmetesse v&otilde;i nende ametliku avaldamise korral nende juurde viite k&auml;esolevale direktiivile. </eesti>
<inglise> The procedure for such a reference shall be adopted by Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellise viitamise viisi n&auml;evad ette liikmesriigid. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall immediately communicate to the Commission all provisions of national law which they adopt in the field covered by this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid edastavad komisjonile viivitamata siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide teksti, mis nad k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga reguleeritavas valdkonnas vastu v&otilde;tavad. </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission shall inform the other Member States thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon teavitab sellest teisi liikmesriike. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive shall enter into force on the day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev direktiiv j&otilde;ustub p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
